text.tspan: I’m Learning:
ROBOTICS/PROGRAMMING
MEET EDWARE
Card 2 of 6
This is EdWare and it is the software used to program the Edison Robot. You can download it from
EDISON
Sushi
http://meetedison.com/robot-programming-software/
or you can use the online editor available from here:
http://edwareapp.com
To get familiar with EdWare and programming, grab icons from the palette on the left and drag them onto
the programming area. Place icons between the 'start' and 'end' icons.
Select an icon and adjust settings in the Icon Property box to control how the Edison responds to that icon.
Use the help text as a guide when programming. Everything you need to know about an icon can be found
here. The variables editor is where you create and view little pieces of Edison's memory.
Q.
What are the names of the four main icon groups?
Using the online editor provides the added benefit of allowing you to store your programs in the 'cloud'
once you've created an account with edwareapp.com. This means you can access your programs from
any computer that has internet access. Bonus!
